description.narrative: By 2018, cross-cutting programmatic activities to promote gender equity and innovation, to monitor program quality, and to build knowledge, are implemented for achieving results in support of children, which contributes to Building Capacity For Evaluation, Cross-Sectoral Monitoring, Data And Situation Analyses, Cross-Sectoral Planning And Programme Reviews, Environmental Sustainability, Evaluation And Research, Gender Discriminatory Roles And Practices, Operations Support To Programme Delivery, Other Cross-Sectoral Programme Areas, Prevention And Response Services For Violence Against Children, Supply And Logistics, Unicef Capacity For Programming On Gender, Unicef Capacity For Supply And Logistics. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Fostering Innovation And Use Of New Technologies, Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2018, 100% of the planned budget is mobilized from donors, and 100% of the expected Program Cooperation results are achieved
